# Makefile & Scripts

- Makefile targets must have a `## Description` comment for the `make help` output.
- Use POSIX `sh` for scripts in `scripts/`, not bash. Shebang: `#!/bin/sh`.
- Keep complex shell logic out of the Makefile -- extract into `scripts/` and call with `sh scripts/foo.sh`.
- Use `@` prefix on Makefile recipes to suppress echo when the output itself is sufficient.
